Photo.Description:
Illustration from the medical and surgical journal of Dr Edward B Bogg, Assistant Surgeon aboard HM Hired surveying vessel Beaver.

On a surveying expedition to British Columbia Bogg was interested in the customs and society of the local Native American tribies including their practice of head flattening.

This picture is captioned &quot;Skull of a Northern Indian from the Stikee River, drawn from actual measurements&quot;
